{
  "text": "In HIV-VL coinfected patients already taking or initiated on ART, this study demonstrated slightly higher overall mortality but substantially reduced relapse rates compared to coinfected patients treated with a lower dose 20-25 mg/kg AmBisome monotherapy, with mortality and relapse rates at 12 months of 11.2% and 6.4% compared to 8.7% and 16.2%, respectively [CITATION_1] . Concurrent tuberculosis was found to be an independent risk factor for overall poor outcome in our multivariable model, similar to other studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . No other sociodemographic or clinical factors were found to be associated with poor outcomes.",
  "correct_citation": {
